    "updated_at": "2015-04-14T01:06:53Z",
    "body": "To me it seems like actually encoding this in a source file is an antipattern? For example how can you guarantee that the library will be at the same location on all systems you're compiling on?\n\nThis does seem to be an unfortunate problem, however, where the full path to the library must be passed to the linker to disambiguate. I do think that using a separate `kind` will be the best way to go here, though, as mixing the two up is bound to cause confusion at some point.\n",
